
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `clear_console` (ya be soorat sade `clear`) safhe terminal ra tamiz mikonad. Yani hameye chizhaii ke ghablan neveshte shode ast, pak mishavad va safhe az aval shoru mishavad. In be shoma komak mikonad ke terminal-e moratab-tari dashte bashid. 🧹

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 Hich gozine khasi nadarad.  Faghat `clear` ya `clear_console` ra vared konid.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ clear
    
    🔹 Safhe terminal tamiz mishavad.

    $ clear_console

    🔹 Hamoon kare `clear` ra anjam midahad.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ ls -l  
    file1.txt  file2.txt
    $ clear
    $  
    
    🔹 Aval listi az file-ha neshan dade mishavad. Ba'd az vared kardane `clear`, hameye chizha pak mishavad va faghat satr-e command badi neshan dade mishavad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `clear_console` command (or simply `clear`) cleans the terminal screen. It erases everything that was previously written, starting the screen from scratch. This helps you have a more organized terminal. 🧹

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 It doesn't have specific options.  Just type `clear` or `clear_console`.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ clear

    🔹 Clears the terminal screen.

    $ clear_console

    🔹 Does the same thing as `clear`.

✅ **Simple Example & Explanation:**

    $ ls -l
    file1.txt  file2.txt
    $ clear
    $

    🔹 First, a list of files is displayed. After entering `clear`, everything is erased, and only the next command line is shown.

